        "client_msg_id": "781e3ed1-9a68-4e07-a3e5-6b2ab7854038",
        "text": "Paraphrasing: the original question was about tools for building DSLs. I know that it is possible to build DSLs without using ASTs, using staged computation. Staged computation, at the level of building DSLs is a different line of reasoning\/problem-solving than is the common approach of using function-based programming (which has grown into functional programming).\nThe AST designs that were shown in this thread were  sufficient, but, they are still ASTs designed using the function-based-infinite-memory mindset.\n<https:\/\/open.substack.com\/pub\/programmingsimplicity\/p\/the-spherical-cows-of-programming?r=1egdky&amp;utm_campaign=post&amp;utm_medium=web&amp;showWelcomeOnShare=true>",
